# Shell scripts and the systemd unit MUST be LF, always.
#
# These are executed on Linux (a Steam Deck). A file committed with CRLF from a Windows checkout
# fails there with the deeply unhelpful `bad interpreter: /usr/bin/env bash^M`, and systemd simply
# refuses to parse the unit. Git currently stores them as LF by luck, not by rule — this makes it
# a rule.
*.sh            text eol=lf
*.service       text eol=lf

# Normalise the rest to LF in the repository, letting Git check out the platform's native endings.
*.cs            text
*.csproj        text
*.md            text
*.json          text
*.yml           text
*.ts            text
*.tsx           text

# PowerShell scripts here must stay ASCII/CRLF-safe on Windows PowerShell 5.1, which reads a
# BOM-less .ps1 as ANSI. Leave them to Git's default handling rather than forcing LF.
*.ps1           text

# Binary — never touch.
*.png           binary
*.ico           binary
*.exe           binary
*.zip           binary
*.tar.gz        binary
